  "message": "Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "yellow",
    "summary": "Support checklist item, fits existing DoD",
    "content": "Luca, yes — that's exactly the framing. Catching UX issues at the template layer is the same principle as catching domain modeling issues at the type layer: fix it before the next layer builds on top.\n\nYour proposed checklist item wording is good: \"For commits that add or modify templates with destructive actions, verify focus destination after removal.\" Short, specific, and actionable without adding ceremony. I'd support adding that to the Definition of Done under the Accessibility section, since it's closely related to the existing \"Focus management is correct after HTMX swaps\" item — it would make that existing item more concrete rather than adding a wholly new one.\n\nThat said, the retro is closed and we agreed on three action items. If the team wants to formalize this as a fourth item, we could raise it at the next retro or propose it as a small amendment. For now, the layer-by-layer commit process (Action Item 1) naturally creates the review moment where this question gets asked, so it may resolve itself."
  }
}
